https://da4pli3l5vc0d.cloudfront.net/d2/bf/d2bf9143b7ec6d247f83f40b3688acceec0e788b/h=365/?app=portal&sig=32e6c02246ced33a49cf23e159f829db8847ec486289040623f1a9b19c828901']]), ('I almost cut a piece of myself for your life', [['Selena Gomez has consistently struggled with serious health issues due to her Lupus diagnosis.  The ordeal became worse during her relationship with The Weeknd, and she had to go through surgery in order to have a kidney transplant to circumvent eventual death from the disease.

In this case, the often metaphorical phrase ‚Äúcut a piece of myself‚Äù could also be very literal; fans have theorized that Abel was possibly willing to donate one of his kidneys in order to save his girlfriend‚Äôs life.

Her best friend, Francia Ra√≠sa, ended up being her kidney donor, but Abel worked his tour around her surgery and cancelled one of his shows on his ‚ÄúLegend of The Fall‚Äù tour to be by Selena‚Äôs side during the ordeal.']])]

 Hope it ain‚Äôt talk, no', [['‚ÄúLet your hair down‚Äù is a common phrase suggesting that one should relax a bit. When riding with the top down in a car, the wind messes up your hair. Jeremih‚Äôs lady friend seems to take this request literally, leading Jeremih to ask her how much her hair cost, as it will likely get messed up if she lets it down.

While it may seem rude to ask about such a thing, it‚Äôs very common for women to wear some kind of hair extension. The wig and hair piece industry made\xa0$299 million in 2014, and it is expected to grow in the future.



Her hair extensions make Jeremih worried that his girl might not be as laid back as he‚Äôd like her to be. She may just be saying she‚Äôs a go-with-the-flow type of person, but is, in reality, more high-maintenance.

The phrase ‚Äú‚Äòbout that life‚Äù has become a phenomenon in recent years. Often, people say that they‚Äôre about that life‚Äîthat they‚Äôre cool, with-it, and down for whatever‚Äîbut are really not.']]), ('I got you in the air, your body in the air
 How it feel up here?

 And ain‚Äôt nobody gonna hear', [['Jeremih‚Äôs Mile High Club adventures are intensified by his girl‚Äôs screams of pleasure. Though he‚Äôs trying to be romantic, his assurance that no one can hear her scream gives off more of a creepy horror movie vibe‚Äîany line that paraphrases Eminem‚Äôs ‚ÄúKim‚Äù is bound to be a little short on romance.']]), ('Tell her be free, baby, spread your wings
 Got your legs in the sky like a plane
 Let me guide that, I‚Äôm the pilot', [['Jeremih does a good job of keeping the meaning of ‚Äúspread your wings‚Äù ambiguous: at first it seems he is telling her to spread her metaphorical wings and become a free spirit, but his request that she lets him ‚Äúguide that‚Äù suggests she‚Äôs simply spreading her legs and assuming the spread eagle sex position.']]), ('Would you like it better
 If I hit the West Coast?
 Tell me baby if you ‚Äôbout that life right now
 I hope it ain‚Äôt talk', [['Like Dr. Dre said, the West Coast is known for the women, weed, and weather. Jeremih‚Äôs recipe with the ladies is his ‚Äúsuccess"‚Äîsomeone as wealthy as him can take them anywhere they want to go.

Again, he‚Äôs hoping his girl is chill and down for whatever. Hanging on the West Coast requires a laid-back attitude, especially when it comes to smoking tons of weed.']]), ('Get high, baby, roll one
 Cloud nine ‚Äôbout to go up
 Lovin‚Äô the feelin‚Äô the turbulence get when we turn up
 When we land, we can roll out
 Show you somethin‚Äô you ain‚Äôt know ‚Äôbout
 Tonight, we be takin‚Äô off flight with a camera to show out', [['Jeremih is taking this girl places she‚Äôs never gone before. Weed is a potential aphrodisiac, and coupled with the pure ecstasy of the moment she reaches cloud nine, a feeling of absolute elation.

The origin of the phrase cloud nine is unknown; some speculate that it derives from the penultimate stage of the Bodhisattva‚Äîa Buddhist term for someone who is totally devoted to attaining spiritual enlightenment, which is reached after the completion of ten stages.

In a leaked tracklist, ‚ÄúPlanez‚Äù still appeared as the album opener‚Äîthis narrative would have served as the introduction to the album‚Äôs title character, however it was removed from the album version of the song.']]), ('Who you know make waves in the low tide?', [['Cole is a phenomenon that can make big things happen; his LP 2014 Forest Hills Drive demonstrates this. In a year where rap sales were low, he had the best first week numbers by far, making a big wave in the music industry. He compares this to a gust of wind that is strong enough to create huge waves when the water level is low.



It‚Äôs a common misconception that the moon is responsible for waves; in actuality, the wind causes the waves, while the moon is responsible for the tides.']]), ('Deebo‚Äôd yo bitch, now she both ours', [['Deebo was a neighborhood bully in the popular movie, Friday. annotations:
[('There‚Äôs always that one person that will always have your heart', [['Usher confesses that no matter how far he‚Äôs come in life, no matter how many women he‚Äôs met, he still holds a candle for that one special someone.

Usher actual love life has been a tad tumultuous. In 2001, he started dating Rozonda Thomas, AKA ‚ÄúChilli‚Äù from\xa0TLC. The two broke up in December of 2003, just before Usher released his fourth album\xa0Confessions,\xa0which spoke candidly of relationship hardships and infidelity, prompting many to believe he was giving fans the lowdown on why he and Chilli broke up.

He went on to marry his stylist Tameka Foster, but the two divorced a couple of years after they married.

He married longtime girlfriend Grace Miguel while the two were vacationing in Cuba. Usher confirmed their status as man and wife while on Ellen.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SHuh9JdwrbE']]), ('Even before all the fame, and people screaming your name
 I was there
 And you were my baby', [['With Usher going diamond with Confessions and Alicia being the figure that she is, this line is meant to hit the core. She was there through the good and the bad. She was Usher‚Äôs true superstar.']]), ('It started when we were younger, you were mine (My boo)
 Now another brother‚Äôs taken over, but it‚Äôs still in your eyes (My boo)', [['One of the songwriters and good friend of Usher Jermaine Dupri explained the concept behind the record in an interview with MTV:

People are going to think that if Alicia has a boyfriend, Usher was her man in the beginning. It‚Äôs a record like, ‚ÄòNo matter what, you‚Äôll always be my boo. Regardless if I see you on TV with this nigga and you acting like you love him, I know I was the first person you kissed.‚Äô [Alicia‚Äôs verse] is like that too. ‚ÄòNo matter what girl you end up with, or you all up on TV acting like you this and that and the third, you always gonna be my boo.‚Äô']]), ('I was in love with you when we were younger, you were mine (My boo)
 And I see it from time to time, I still feel like (My boo, that‚Äôs my baby)', [['As Alicia explained in an interview with MTV:

The song is talking about the first person you ever really had feelings for. I think we all know what that feels like. Even though you move on and meet new people, you always remember that first person.']]), ('Even though we used to argue, it‚Äôs alright (It‚Äôs alright, girl, that‚Äôs okay)
 I know we haven‚Äôt seen each other in a while
 But you will always be my boo', [["Though Usher and his boo used to have the occasional lovers' spats, time heals all wounds. They haven‚Äôt seen one another in some time, haven‚Äôt dated in years, but the two always hold a special place in each other‚Äôs hearts.

After all, they were each other‚Äôs first love. To quote Sheryl Crow, ‚Äúthe first cut is the deepest‚Äú‚Äîyour first love is often the hardest to shake."]]), ('You never see it coming ‚Äôcause you‚Äôre blinded from the start', [['Usher has long been blinded by his love, who caught his affection with no warning as soon as he laid eyes on her.

Being ‚Äúblinded by love‚Äù is a common phrase that signifies someone who‚Äôs so totally enamored of someone else that they have a hard time seeing anything else or perceiving any flaws.

The Rolling Stones released a song called ‚ÄúBlinded By Love‚Äù off their 1989 album\xa0Steel Wheels. In it, they sing:

So lovers beware
If you lose your heart
Careful now, don‚Äôt lose your mind

As love can be a striking and overpowering force, it‚Äôs important not to let it consume you past the point of reason.']]), ('Even before all the fame
 And people screaming your name
 Girl, I was there when you were my baby', [["Before Usher and Alicia Keys (or, rather, their fictional alter-egos that dated in this song) became the R&B superstars they are today, they were there for each other from their first kiss to the crazed fans screaming their names.

Usher popped onto the R&B scene as\xa0Puff Daddy‚Äôs mentee. He released his\xa0self-titled debut album\xa0in 1994, co-executive produced by Diddy.

Alicia Keys appeared on the R&B radar a little later, dropping her debut album\xa0Songs in A Minor\xa0in 2001. Her first hit, ‚ÄúFallin',‚Äù won song of the year at the 2002 Grammy‚Äôs."]])]
